* Jeremie Koenig works on Java on Hurd as his GSoC project, bringing not only Java to the Hurd but also adding missing parts in Hurd pthreads which helps gcj - as well as fixing a build problem of emacs-23.3². As first treat he added signal improvements³.
    - ¹: http://www.bddebian.com/~hurd-web/user/jkoenig/java/
    - ²: http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/bug-hurd/2011-05/msg00017.html
    - ³: http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/bug-hurd/2011-05/msg00182.html

* Samuel Thibault created the first Debian GNU/Hurd CD set with a graphical installer http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/bug-hurd/2011-05/msg00189.html

* Tanguy LE CARROUR offered to sponsor some Hurd work, and followed up on his offer by adding Hurd bounties on FOSS factory - claim them if you can! http://www.gnu.org/software/hurd/news/2011-05-02-foss_factory.html

* Samuel Thibault fixed a port-leak in file_reparent which got visible in the debian builder. http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/bug-hurd/2011-05/msg00025.html

* The respective next MotH is now prepared [[publicly_in_the_wiki|contributing/web_pages/news/moth_next]], lowering the barrier of entry for news-writing. Feel free to [[contribute|contributing/web_pages/news]].

